  "prompt": "How long does it take to become a full stack web developer?",
  "response": "The time to become a full stack web developer can vary depending on several factors:\n\n1. Prior Experience\n- No coding experience: 6-12 months\n- Some programming knowledge: 3-6 months\n- Computer science background: 2-4 months\n\n2. Learning Path Options\n- Coding Bootcamp: 3-6 months (intensive)\n- Self-taught: 6-12 months\n- Online courses: 6-12 months\n- Computer Science degree: 2-4 years\n\n3. Learning Intensity\n- Part-time learning: 12-18 months\n- Full-time dedicated learning: 6-9 months\n- Immersive/intensive learning: 3-6 months\n\n4. Skills to Learn\n- HTML/CSS\n- JavaScript\n- Frontend frameworks (React, Vue, Angular)\n- Backend technologies (Node.js, Python, Ruby)\n- Database management\n- Version control\n- Basic design principles\n- Server management\n\n5. Practical Factors\n- Individual learning pace\n- Time dedicated to learning\n- Quality of learning resources\n- Practice and project complexity\n\nRecommended approach:\n- Start with fundamentals\n- Build projects\n- Create a strong portfolio\n- Continuously learn and update skills\n\nAverage realistic timeline: 9-12 months of consistent, focused learning.",
